                  <p class="date">26 May 2005</p>
                  <p class="author">by Noel</p>
                </div>

                <div class="span8">
                  <h2>
                    <a
                      href="/untyping/2005/05/26/plt-blog-watch/"
                      rel="bookmark"
                      title="Permanent Link to PLT Blog Watch">PLT Blog Watch</a
                    >
                  </h2>

                  <div class="entry">
                    <p>
                      I’ve just become aware that a lot of the <a
                        href="http://www.plt-scheme.org/">PLT</a
                      > crew are keeping blogs. Worth checking out if <a
                        href="http://lambda-the-ultimate.org/"
                        >Lambda the Ultimate</a
                      > doesn’t provide you with enough daily programming
                      language theory are:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                      <li>
                        <a href="http://calculist.blogspot.com/"
                          >The Little Calculist</a
                        > (Dave Herman)
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <a href="http://keepworkingworkerbee.blogspot.com/"
                          >Keep Working, Worker Bee!</a
                        > (Jacob Matthews)
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <a href="http://www.bloglines.com/blog/wand"
                          >Mitch’s Clippings</a
                        > (Mitch Wand)
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                      Jacob’s blog is particularly interesting to me for two
                      reasons:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                      <li>
                        He’s talking a bit about commercial applications of PLT
                        Scheme, something that we’re trying to do at <a
                          href="http://www.untyped.com/">Untyped</a
                        >
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        He’s got a <a
                          href="http://people.cs.uchicago.edu/~jacobm/pubs/topsl.pdf"
                          >great paper</a
                        > showing how a pile of programming language theory can
                        be applied to solve a problem way better than anyone
                        else has solved it before, which is something we’re<em
                          >really</em
                        > into!
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>

                  <p class="tags">
                    Posted in
                    <a href="/untyping/category/general/" rel="category tag"
                      >General</a
                    >
                    |
                    <span
                      >Comments Off<span class="screen-reader-text">
                        on PLT Blog Watch</span
                      ></span
                    >
                  </p>
