                  <div class="entry">
                    <p>
                      <a href="http://www.culturedcode.com/xyle/">Xyle</a> looks
                      like a nifty tool for working out how a CSS design was
                      created. It only works on Safari, so for most people the <a
                        href="http://chrispederick.com/work/firefox/webdeveloper/"
                        >Web Developer plugin for Firefox</a
                      > will be more useful. Xyle does have a few features that
                      WD doesn’t, so if you have Safari and the $15 I’d say it’s
                      worth it.
                    </p>
